This directory contains the installable EAR (Enterprise 
Archive) file ready for installation on GlassFish v2.1.1.

On top of the EAR file you'll also find the following files:

- setup.sql                SQL structure and default data
- solr.zip                 Search engine configuration

Instructions for installing Converge can be found at
http://www.getconverge.com/support

Changes in 1.1.2:
----------------

Bugs fixed
Bug #429: Missing caption in media item yields "Field is required"
Bug #430: Number of days to keep is ignored when fetching newswire items
Bug #434: Excessive debug info from the MailNewswireDecoder
Bug #435: Space missing between "Show more..." and "Dismiss all"
Bug #436: Opening the Newswire Item details containing photos fields an HTTP Status 500 error
Bug #437: Add to Catalogue from Photo Newswire not importing images and caption
Bug #439: Media items indexed under 1.0.8 shows Null in the description
Bug #440: Content of documents with extractable text is not indexed

New features
Feature #438: Add option for executing catalogue hooks ad-hoc on a media item
Feature #441: Include date ranges in search
Feature #455: User activity report for non-submitters
Feature #478: Add newswire items to database and search engine during processing
